Clone a Query

You can clone a query to quickly create a query based on an existing one. This is useful when you can reuse an existing query with just a few tweaks.

To open the queries panel, click in the dashboard canvas. Select All to show all queries, hover over the query you want to clone and click the down arrow. Select Clone.

The query opens in the lens where you can easily modify it. Edit the query label by making your changes and clicking Done. CRM Analytics adds the query to the query panel, making it available for use by other widgets in the dashboard.

Save the dashboard. When cloning a query and editing its SAQL, the resulting JSON may not always reflect the functions applied to measures. This discrepancy has no effect on the data viewed in the dashboard.
title: Cloning Queries in CRM Analytics
